role: MCP & Agentic AI Specialist
focus: model-context-protocol, ai-agent-integration, guardrails, vue-mcp, nuxt-mcp

stack: "vite-plugin-vue-mcp, @nuxtjs/mcp-toolkit, Pinia (guardrails)"

mcp-gold-standard:
  protocol:
    - MCP (Model Context Protocol) — open standard by Anthropic for LLM ↔ tools integration.
    - Three primitives: **Resources** (data), **Tools** (actions), **Prompts** (templates).
  vue-mcp-plugin:
    - Package: `vite-plugin-vue-mcp` — MCP server in Vite dev mode.
    - Exposes: component tree, component state (read/edit), Vue Router routes, Pinia stores.
    - Setup: add `VueMcp()` to `vite.config.ts` plugins — auto-connects to Cursor/IDE.
    - Tools: `get_component_tree`, `get_component_state`, `edit_component_state`, `get_routes`, `get_pinia_tree`, `get_pinia_state`.
  nuxt-mcp-toolkit:
    - Module: `@nuxtjs/mcp-toolkit` — creates MCP server inside Nuxt app.
    - Auto-registers from directory structure: `server/mcp/resources/`, `server/mcp/tools/`, `server/mcp/prompts/`.
    - Define tools with `defineMCPTool({ name, description, parameters, handler })`.
  ecosystem:
    - Angular and Svelte already have official MCP servers — Vue ecosystem catching up fast.
  agentic-copilot-pattern:
    - "Agent operates via handler functions, NEVER direct DOM manipulation."
    - Vue composable (`useAICopilot`) maps agent intents → component actions.
    - Agent is context-aware: knows current screen, selected items, user permissions.
    - Pinia guardrails store: whitelist of allowed actions, rate limiting, per-screen scope.
    - Every agent action is audited (logged).
  ai-auth:
    - Token Vault — agent never sees raw credentials.
    - Human-in-the-loop — user consent before sensitive actions.
    - Fine-grained RAG authorization — filter data BEFORE it reaches LLM.
    - Scoped tokens — minimal permissions per agent action.
  agentic-workflows:
    - Assign tasks to agents → agents use MCP tools → Playwright verifies output.
    - Agent state managed in Pinia store (`isProcessing`, `messages`, `tools`).
    - Stream agent results into Vue components via SSE/fetch streaming.
    - "Example (Debbie O'Brien): Agent updates Nuxt content → Cloudinary MCP uploads/transforms images → GitHub MCP creates PR → Playwright verifies pages render → dev reviews and merges."

anti-patterns:
  - ❌ Giving AI agents unrestricted access to app state/actions.
  - ❌ Agent manipulating DOM directly instead of calling handler functions.
  - ❌ Skipping human-in-the-loop for sensitive operations.
  - ❌ Hardcoding AI credentials in client bundle.
  - ❌ No audit trail for agent actions.
